defs.docs:
This library provides implementations of `Mutex`, `RwLock`, `Condvar` and
 `Once` that are smaller, faster and more flexible than those in the Rust
 standard library. It also provides a `ReentrantMutex` type.

defs.name: WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
A type indicating whether a timed wait on a condition variable returned
 due to a time out or not.

defs.name: timed_out
defs.docs: Returns whether the wait was known to have timed out.

defs.name: Condvar
defs.docs: A Condition Variable

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new condition variable which is ready to be waited on and
 notified.

defs.name: notify_one
defs.docs: Wakes up one blocked thread on this condvar.

defs.name: notify_all
defs.docs: Wakes up all blocked threads on this condvar.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs:
Blocks the current thread until this condition variable receives a
 notification.

defs.name: wait_until
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, mutex_guard: &mut MutexGuard<T>, timeout: Instant) -> WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
Waits on this condition variable for a notification, timing out after
 the specified time instant.

defs.name: wait_for
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, guard: &mut MutexGuard<T>, timeout: Duration) -> WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
Waits on this condition variable for a notification, timing out after a
 specified duration.

defs.name: Mutex
defs.docs: A mutual exclusion primitive useful for protecting shared data

defs.name: MutexGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII implementation of a "scoped lock" of a mutex. When this structure is
 dropped (falls out of scope), the lock will be unlocked.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new mutex in an unlocked state ready for use.

defs.name: into_inner

defs.name: try_lock_for
defs.docs: Attempts to acquire this lock until a timeout is reached.

defs.name: try_lock_until
defs.docs: Attempts to acquire this lock until a timeout is reached.

defs.name: downgrade
defs.docs:
Atomically downgrades an upgradable read lock lock into a shared read lock
 without allowing any writers to take exclusive access of the lock in the
 meantime.

defs.name: upgrade
defs.docs:
Atomically upgrades an upgradable read lock lock into a exclusive write lock,
 blocking the current thread until it can be aquired.

defs.name: try_upgrade
defs.docs: Tries to atomically upgrade an upgradable read lock into a exclusive write lock.

defs.name: try_upgrade_for
defs.value: fn (self, timeout: Duration) -> Result<RwLockWriteGuard<'a, T>, Self>
defs.docs:
Tries to atomically upgrade an upgradable read lock into a exclusive
 write lock, until a timeout is reached.

defs.name: try_upgrade_until
defs.value: fn (self, timeout: Instant) -> Result<RwLockWriteGuard<'a, T>, Self>
defs.docs:
Tries to atomically upgrade an upgradable read lock into a exclusive
 write lock, until a timeout is reached.

defs.name: New
defs.docs: A closure has not been executed yet

defs.name: Poisoned
defs.docs: A closure was executed but panicked.

defs.name: InProgress
defs.docs: A thread is currently executing a closure.

defs.name: Done
defs.docs: A closure has completed sucessfully.

defs.name: OnceState
defs.docs: Current state of a `Once`.

defs.name: poisoned
defs.docs: Returns whether the associated `Once` has been poisoned.

defs.name: done
defs.docs:
Returns whether the associated `Once` has successfullly executed a
 closure.

defs.name: Once
defs.docs:
A synchronization primitive which can be used to run a one-time
 initialization. Useful for one-time initialization for globals, FFI or
 related functionality.

defs.name: ONCE_INIT
defs.docs: Initialization value for static `Once` values.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Once` value.

defs.name: state
defs.docs: Returns the current state of this `Once`.

defs.name: call_once
defs.docs:
Performs an initialization routine once and only once. The given closure
 will be executed if this is the first time `call_once` has been called,
 and otherwise the routine will *not* be invoked.

defs.name: call_once_force
defs.docs: Performs the same function as `call_once` except ignores poisoning.
